INSTALL:
extract the archive, then copy "usr" into the root: "sudo cp usr / -R"

Known dependences: Python-appindicator


FAQ

Q: When I use a non default icon theme, the cHD icons are too bright to see.
A: You should get the icon theme name (e.g. by watching the terminal output by indicator-crystalhd),
then copy the /usr/share/indicator-crystalhd/Radiance folder to /usr/share/indicator-crystalhd/<theme-name>.
